At least 11 premature babies were killed Wednesday in a fire that tore through one of Baghdad&#8217;s largest maternity hospitals, medical and security sources said.Health ministry spokesman Ahmed al-Rudeini told AFP the blaze at the Yarmouk hospital in west Baghdad was started by an electrical fault.He added that 29 other infants in Yarmouk &#8220;were evacuated to other hospitals in the capital.&#8221;An official at Iraq&#8217;s interior ministry confirmed the death toll from the fire, adding that three other babies were being treated for smoke inhalation.Many of Baghdad&#8217;s public hospitals are considered of poor quality, pushing a number of Iraqis to seek private healthcare.-AFP